<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12019r"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12019r">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12019r"> 19(r)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> la cloche Rollon</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"> Cent ans avaient donc suffi pour r&eacute;aliser la pr&eacute;diction du prieur de Saint-Michel. Le descendant des Vikings, le pirate Rollon, fut un de ceux qui aid&egrave;rent &agrave; &eacute;lever la basilique du Mont par ses riches dotations, et la grosse cloche de l&apos;abbaye, celle qu&apos;on sonnait en cas d&apos;alarme, prit le nom de <mark>cloche Rollon</mark>. <br><font color="green">[One hundred years were enough for the prophecy of the prior of Saint-Michel to come true. The descendant of the Vikings, the pirate Rollo, was one of those who helped to erect a basilica on the Mount with rich donations, and the large bell of the abbey, the one that was used in case of emergency, was called the Rollo bell.]</font> <small> &Eacute;douard Schur&eacute;, <a name="ESLL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ESLL"><cite title="source">Les Grandes L&eacute;gendes de France</cite></a> (1892) 171</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c12002d" href="c12all.htm#c12002d">VI.C.12:002(d)</a></mm></dd> </dd></dl>
